Cross-activity summary
Core merchant activity system
The merchant workflow is not a single tool flow. It is an activity system with four major activities:
1.	Calibrate daily grain buying position
2.	Evaluate whether producer-level targeting is worth doing
3.	Prepare and package weekly strategy for originators
4.	Review outcomes and update future strategy
Important lens-specific pattern
The most important structural pattern is:
•	Pre-tool cognition is substantial
•	market framing
•	risk assessment
•	prioritization
•	communication setup
•	In-tool work is analytical but incomplete
•	scenario inspection
•	competitor comparison
•	targeting attempts
•	Post-tool work is where execution and learning really happen
•	spreadsheet packaging
•	emailing / talking to originators
•	reading contract emails
•	reconstructing outcomes
That means the pricing tool currently supports only part of the full activity system.
 
Highest-value contradictions surfaced by the lens
1.	Useful logic vs hard interaction
2.	Targeting is valuable vs targeting is too painful to use
3.	Weekly strategy exists vs execution support is disconnected
4.	Outcome learning is necessary vs feedback is fragmented
5.	Tool should support actionability vs spreadsheet is still the real workbench
 
